                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>This Sanskrit grant was issued from the royal camp at <hi rend="bold">Mēnmātura,</hi> in the <hi rend="bold">5th year</hi> of the reign of the Pallava king <hi rend="bold">Mahārāja Siṁhavarman,</hi> son of Yuva-Mahārāja Vishṇugōpa, grandson of Mahārāja Skandavarman and great-grandson of Mahārāja Vīravarman. It registers the grant of the village <hi rend="bold">Pīkira</hi> in Muṇḍa-rāshṭra, to Vilāsaśarman of the Kāśyapa-(gōtra) and of the Taittirīya-(śākhā).</p>	
                            
